Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.69,0:01:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第三集
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.94,0:01:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的身世很神秘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We were born into a mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.78,0:01:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,這一直困擾著我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that has haunted us
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.82,0:01:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,自從人類誕生就是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}since at least as long as we've been human.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.82,0:01:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,在這個星空覆蓋下的小星球上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We awakened on this tiny world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.46,0:01:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我們開始有了意識\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}beneath a blanket of stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.39,0:01:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同被遺棄在門口的嬰兒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like an abandoned baby left on a doorstep
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.73,0:02:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有留下隻字片語\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without a note to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.23,0:02:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,告訴我們是誰 我們從哪裏來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where we came from, who we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.90,0:02:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的世界會是怎樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how our universe came to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.31,0:02:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在宇宙中是否還有其他同類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And with no idea how to end our cosmic isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.61,0:02:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我們必須自己找出答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've had to figure it all out for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.92,0:02:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我們最大的財富\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Best thing we had going for us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.99,0:02:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我們的智慧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was our intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.46,0:02:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,特別是識別規律的天賦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}especially our gift for pattern recognition,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,經過遠古以來進化過程的改造\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sharpened over eons of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.46,0:02:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那些擅長區分獵物和猛獸的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ones who were good at spotting prey and predator,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.63,0:02:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,擅長識別有毒的食物的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}telling poisonous plants from the nourishing ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他們活下去並繁衍的幾率更大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they had a better chance to live and reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.20,0:02:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他們倖存下來 並把識別規律的基因傳下去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They survived and passed on those genes for pattern recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.04,0:02:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,優勢顯而易見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with its obvious advantages.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.14,0:02:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的不同文化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cultures all over the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.71,0:02:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,都是仰望同一個星空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}looked up at the same stars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.38,0:02:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,然後做出不同的解讀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and found different pictures there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.16,0:03:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我們用這種天賦在自然界中尋找規律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We used this gift for recognizing patterns in nature
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.63,0:03:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,解讀天空中的年歷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to read the calendar in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,寫在星空中的信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The messages written in the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.04,0:03:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,告訴我們的祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}told our forefathers and mothers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.90,0:03:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,何時安營  何時啟程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when to camp and when to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.81,0:03:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,獸群何時遷徙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the migratory herds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.41,0:03:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,何時下雨  何時天寒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and when the rains and the cold would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.41,0:03:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,何時他們可以停下來休息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when they would cease for a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.68,0:03:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,當他們觀察恆星間的運動與地球上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When they observed the direct connection between the motions of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.22,0:03:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,生命週期變化之間的直接聯繫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the seasonal cycles of life on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.32,0:03:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他們很自然地得出結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they concluded, naturally,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,天上發生的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that what happens up there
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.16,0:03:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,必然和地球上發生的事情息息相關\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}must be directed at us down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.56,0:03:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,也有道理 對吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It makes sense, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.39,0:03:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,如果把天空看成日曆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If the sky was a calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.16,0:03:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,有人在上面貼上一張便簽紙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and somebody stuck a Post-it note on top of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,除了傳達信息還會是什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what else could it be but a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.33,0:03:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,所以  當天空的秩序被突然打破時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And so, when the heavenly order was suddenly violated
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.54,0:03:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,比如 當彗星劃過天際時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the apparition of a comet in the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.34,0:03:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,人們就會和自身聯繫起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they took it personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.54,0:03:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,也不能怪他們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Can we really blame them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.45,0:03:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,那時 對於所發生的事情也沒有其他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Back then, they had no other logical explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.05,0:03:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,符合邏輯的解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for what was happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.55,0:03:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,那是很久以前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was long before
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.18,0:04:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人會認為地球是個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}anyone had yet to imagine Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,傾斜自轉的行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a spinning planet with a tilted axis,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.26,0:04:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,繞著太陽公轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}revolving around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,每種文化中的古人都犯過相同的錯誤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every ancient human culture made the same mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.69,0:04:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星一定是來自眾神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a comet must be a message,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,或某一個神的旨意\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sent by the gods... or one particular god.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎是必然的  我們的祖先認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And almost invariably, our ancestors concluded
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,大事不妙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the news was not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.91,0:04:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,不論你是古阿茲特克人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It didn't matter if you were an ancient Aztec,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,古英國人 古巴比倫人  古印度人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Anglo-Saxon, Babylonian, Hindu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.38,0:04:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星都是毀滅的前兆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Comets were portents of doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.78,0:04:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,僅有的不同是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The only difference among them
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.39,0:04:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,災難預報的精確程度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was the precise nature of the coming disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,災禍 源自希臘語中的 災星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Dis-aster," as in the Greek word for "bad star."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.29,0:04:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,對東非的馬塞人來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To the Masai of East Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.43,0:04:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星意味著饑荒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a comet meant famine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.66,0:04:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,對南非的祖魯人來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To the Zulu in the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.50,0:04:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,意味著戰爭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it meant war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.07,0:04:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,對於西非的迦納人來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To the Eghap people of the west,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,意味著瘟疫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it meant disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.11,0:04:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,對薩伊人來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To the Djaga of Zaire,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.11,0:04:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}薩伊人（剛果）
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.34,0:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,特指 天花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}specifically "smallpox."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:04:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,對於他們的鄰居 陸巴人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To their neighbors, the Luba,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.34,0:05:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星預示著領袖之死\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a comet foretold the death of a leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.12,0:05:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,古代中國人有著驚人的系統分類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ancient Chinese were remarkably systematic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.12,0:05:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,大約公元前1400年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Starting in roughly 1400 BC,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.02,0:05:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他們就開始了對彗星的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they began recording and cataloguing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.43,0:05:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,記錄和分類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the apparitions of comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,三尾彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A three-tailed comet
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.60,0:05:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,意味著國家的災難\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}meant calamity for the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.36,0:05:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,四尾彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A four-tailed comet
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.87,0:05:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,標誌著瘟疫降臨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}signified an epidemic was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.17,0:05:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,人類識別規律的天賦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The human talent for pattern recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.00,0:05:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,是把雙刃劍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a two-edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.04,0:05:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我們尤其擅長尋找規律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're especially good at finding patterns,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.54,0:05:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,哪怕無中生有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even when they aren't really there--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.54,0:05:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,或者 牽強附會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}something known as "false pattern recognition."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我們渴望證明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We hunger for significance,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,人類的存在對這個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for signs that our personal existence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.79,0:05:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有著重大的意義\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is of special meaning to the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.46,0:05:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,說到底 我們的渴望\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To that end, we're all too eager
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.86,0:05:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,使我們寧願相信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to deceive ourselves and others,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.00,0:05:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,烤麵包上出現的聖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to discern a sacred image in a grilled cheese sandwich
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,或者彗星帶著上帝的旨意\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or find a divine warning in a comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.67,0:06:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,今天 我們已經\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Today, we know exactly where comets come from
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.41,0:06:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,清楚知道了彗星的本質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and what they're made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.68,0:06:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的想像之舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our Ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.52,0:06:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,由科學和好奇共同驅動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}fueled by equal parts of science and wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.35,0:06:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,可以帶我們遊歷任何時空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can take us anywhere in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,可以走的比光速還快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can travel faster than light
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.83,0:06:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,可以呈現肉眼無法看見的事物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and render visible those things that cannot be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.23,0:06:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,將我們進入一條神秘的溪流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's carrying us to a mysterious realm
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.53,0:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,距離太陽一光年的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that lies one light-year from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.37,0:06:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,眾多的星體為何聚集\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is this swarm of worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.44,0:06:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是由外星生物安排的嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Was it organized by alien beings?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.17,0:06:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,萬有引力而已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.61,0:06:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,歷年的積雪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These are the snows of yesteryear,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,山峰般的寒冰和岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}drifting mountains of ice and rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽系誕生時的剩餘產物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the preserved remnants of the birth of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.95,0:06:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,組成了 奧爾特雲團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's called the Oort Cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.19,0:06:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,以荷蘭天文學家奧爾特命名\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}after Jan Oort, the Dutch astronomer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他在1950年就預言了這個雲團的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who foretold its existence back in 1950.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他原本想解決一個悖論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was trying to solve a paradox.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:06:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星有很多種消亡的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's so many ways for comets to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,因為他們會穿過行星的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because they cross the orbits of planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,經常發生碰撞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}comets frequently collide with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.70,0:07:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星很大程度上由冰組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Comets are largely made of ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.71,0:07:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 每次接近太陽時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so every time they come near the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.54,0:07:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他們會蒸發掉一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they lose a part of themselves through evaporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.54,0:07:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,這個過程重複幾千次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And after several thousand trips,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.95,0:07:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的冰 蒸發了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their ice is all gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.98,0:07:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,殘餘的彗星就是現在的小行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and what remains of the comet is now an asteroid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.05,0:07:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星被太陽系的引力場排斥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Comets can be gravitationally ejected from the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.99,0:07:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,流放至太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and exiled into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.96,0:07:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,無論如何\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And yet, somehow,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.59,0:07:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星總會回來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the comets keep coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,奧爾特和其他天文學家自忖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oort and other astronomers wondered,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,這些彗星都是哪裏來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Where do all the comets come from?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,奧爾特通過計算新彗星出現的比率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oort calculated the rate at which new comets appear
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.60,0:07:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,得出結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and concluded that there must be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.61,0:07:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,由數量極多的彗星組成一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a vast, spherical swarm of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.41,0:07:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,直徑達到幾光年的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a few light-years across,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.61,0:07:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,園球狀包圍太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}surrounding the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,奧爾特的理論時至今日依然成立\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oort's logic still holds up,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.58,0:07:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,哪怕是幾十年後  我們對彗星和太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even after all the discoveries we've made about comets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,有了更多的認識的今天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the solar system in the many decades since.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.79,0:07:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,不過  奧爾特雲團是個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And yet, the Oort Cloud is a sight
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.79,0:08:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,無人能看到的景象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that no one has ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我們也不行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nor could we.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那裏漆黑一片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's dark out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.27,0:08:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,最近的兩個彗星間的距離就如同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And each comet is about as far from its closest neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.37,0:08:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,地球到土星的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the Earth is from Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,但是 科學給我們特殊的能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But science gives us special powers of our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.54,0:08:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,科學給了奧爾特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It gave Jan Oort
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,預見的天賦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the gift of prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,奧爾特也是第一個正確估計出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oort was also the first to correctly estimate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.05,0:08:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽到銀河系中心的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the distance between the Sun and the center of our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,這是很了不起的成就\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's a big deal--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.49,0:08:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,找到了我們在銀河系的位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}finding out where we are in the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.85,0:08:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our star is about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,距離中心3萬光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}30,000 light-years from the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,奧爾特也是首個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oort was also
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.46,0:08:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,使用射電望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the first guy to use a radio telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,繪製出了銀河系的螺旋結構\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to map the galaxy's spiral structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.63,0:08:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,並且 他發現銀河系的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he discovered that the center of our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.73,0:08:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,發生著一連串極大的爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was a place of titanic explosions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.17,0:08:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,這是第一個跡象 顯示出那裏可能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the first indication that there might have been
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.91,0:08:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,暗藏著一個巨大的黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a supermassive black hole lurking there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.98,0:08:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 我們中的很多人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Does the fact that most of us know
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.64,0:08:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,知道著名殺人魔的名字\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the names of mass murderers,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,卻從沒聽說過奧爾特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but never heard of Jan Oort,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.71,0:08:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,人性就是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}say anything about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.86,0:09:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,奧爾特雲團是如此巨大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Oort Cloud is so enormous
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星要用100萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that it takes one of its comets about a million years
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,才能繞太陽一圈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to complete a single trip around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.27,0:09:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,在這裏 太陽系的邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Out here, at the far edge of the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.51,0:09:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,即使擦肩而過的星星產生的輕微引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even a little tug from the gravity of a passing star
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.68,0:09:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,也會使這些彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can liberate some of these comets
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.68,0:09:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,擺脫太陽引力的束縛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from their gravitational bondage to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.68,0:09:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,一些彗星被拋出太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some comets are flung out of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.75,0:09:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,從此在星際空間遊蕩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to wander interstellar space.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.22,0:09:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的一些彗星 卻有著不同的命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But for others, there's a different fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.43,0:09:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆彗星被拋向太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This one is plunging towards the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,在無阻力的自由落體中不斷加速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gaining speed in an unbroken free fall
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.14,0:09:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,一直持續幾十萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that lasts hundreds of thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,當海王星的引力再次吸引它時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Neptune's gravity gives it another tug,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.71,0:10:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,它的軌跡發生了小小的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there's a small change in course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.21,0:10:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,強大的木星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mighty Jupiter, the most massive
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.78,0:10:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽系中質量最大的物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}object in our solar system--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.22,0:10:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,除太陽以外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}other than the Sun-- attracts the comet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.92,0:10:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,用它強大的引力再次改變彗星的軌跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with its powerful gravitational pull, bending its path.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.73,0:10:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,當這顆彗星到達太陽系的核心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When our comet reaches the inner solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.40,0:10:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽的熱量烘烤著它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}heat from the Sun bakes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,一場美麗的轉變開始了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A beautiful transformation begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,被煙燻黑的貧瘠冰山\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The barren, sooty iceberg
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,變幻出灼熱的光暈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}now sports a glowing halo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.79,0:10:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,還有彗尾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and a tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,這些粉塵層描述著大約40億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These layers tell the story of how the comet was made,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.13,0:10:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星產生的過程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some four billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.97,0:11:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在4萬代人的歷史中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}During the 40,000 generations of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.68,0:11:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,至少有大約10萬次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there must have been roughly 100,000 apparitions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,耀眼的彗星劃過天際\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a bright comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.05,0:11:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那個時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我們只能仰望  不禁的驚嘆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the best we could do was look up in helpless wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,無助的人們不知所措\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}prisoners of Earth with nowhere to turn
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.29,0:11:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,除了恐懼和悔恨 沒有更好的辦法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for an explanation beyond our guilt and our fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.06,0:11:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,後來 兩個人的友情為人類的思想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But then a friendship began between two men that led
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,帶來了翻天覆地的革命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a permanent revolution in human thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.14,0:11:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,艾薩克·牛頓和愛德蒙·哈雷 也是始料未及\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton and Edmond Halley could not know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的研究成果將我們從\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but their collaboration would ultimately set us free
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆小星球的局限中徹底解放\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from our long confinement on this tiny world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.08,0:11:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,1664年的這顆彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Comet of 1664
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.88,0:11:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,令整個歐洲恐懼顫慄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sent shivers of dread throughout Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,隨後發生的大瘟疫和倫敦大火災\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the terror seemed justified when the Plague
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.05,0:12:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,恰巧印證了人們的恐懼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the Great Fire of London followed soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.62,0:12:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,那血色的長髮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There, with long bloody hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.09,0:12:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,耀眼的星辰威脅整個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a blazing star threatens the world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,帶來饑荒  瘟疫 戰爭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with famine, plague and war.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.73,0:12:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,王子們的死亡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To princes, it spells death...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.57,0:12:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,王國多了無數的墓碑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to kingdoms, many crosses...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.64,0:12:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,不可避免的財產損失\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to all estates, inevitable losses...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.95,0:12:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,腐爛的牧群\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to herdsmen, rot,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.98,0:12:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,顆粒無收的莊稼漢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to plowmen, hapless seasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,海上的風暴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to sailors, it brings storms,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.46,0:12:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,暴動的市民\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to cities, civil treasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.50,0:12:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但有一個孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But for one child,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.87,0:12:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,並不覺得彗星有那麼恐怖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the comet was not the least bit frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:13:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,對他來說 只是驚奇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For him, it was a thing of wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.81,0:13:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,和我們一樣  愛德蒙·哈雷生性好奇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like all of us, Edmond Halley was born curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.88,0:13:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,哇塞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hell's bells!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.02,0:13:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他很幸運  他的父親支持並鼓勵他的求知慾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was lucky to have a father who encouraged and nurtured his curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.86,0:13:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,給他買了最好的科學儀器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}buying him the best scientific instruments
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,資助他的探險考察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and even funding his expedition
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.83,0:13:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,為了畫出第一張精確的南半球星空圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to make the first accurate star map of the Southern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.87,0:13:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷20歲時從牛津輟學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley dropped out of Oxford when he was 20,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,去了聖赫勒拿島\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and sailed to St. Helena,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,一個位於赤道以南  非洲的西海岸的小島\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an island below the equator, off the west coast of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.55,0:13:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,哇塞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hell's bells.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.35,0:13:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,問題是 沒人告訴哈雷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The problem was, nobody told Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,島上的天氣狀況是如此糟糕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the weather on St. Helena was generally lousy;
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.35,0:13:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他用了12個月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it took him 12 frustrating months
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.36,0:13:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,才觀測到足夠的南半球星星來繪製完整的星圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to observe enough southern stars to make a complete map.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,古希臘的眾神和英雄人物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The gods and heroes of ancient Greece were now joined
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.40,0:13:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,由虛構的圖形將他們匯聚在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the mythic figures of a new world and age,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.54,0:13:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,巨喙鳥  指南針  天堂鳥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a toucan, a compass, a bird of paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.58,0:14:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,當哈雷帶著《南天星表》回到家時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Halley came home with the other half of the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.62,0:14:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他的星空圖造成了轟動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}his map created a sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.59,0:14:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,商人和探險家可以根據隨處可見的星星導航\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now merchants and explorers could navigate by the stars visible anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.52,0:14:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,當時 倫敦的皇家學會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At the time, the World Society of London
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.59,0:14:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,是世界上科學發現的集散地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was the world's clearinghouse of scientific discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,它的格言是 不人云亦云\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its motto, "Nullius in verba,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.57,0:14:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,總結出了科學方法的中心思想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sums up the heart of the scientific method.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,它是拉丁語中的 親自求證\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's Latin for "see for yourself."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,換言之 質疑權威\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In other words, "question authority."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.97,0:14:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷的星圖引起了學會實驗室負責人的注意\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley's star maps caught the attention of the Society's Curator of Experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.95,0:14:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我也想讓你看看他的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'd show him to you if I could,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.71,0:14:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,但羅伯特·胡克並沒有留下任何的肖像畫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but no portrait of Robert Hooke exists from his time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,只有他的事跡口耳相傳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}only the verbal descriptions of his contemporaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.79,0:14:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,他們說他 瘦弱 駝背 醜陋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They called him "lean, bent, ugly."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.09,0:14:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他可能是最有創造性的天才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was possibly the most inventive person who ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.23,0:14:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,不論他的外表如何\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And despite his appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.99,0:14:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他在當時的倫敦炙手可熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he was the most sought-after party guest in all of London.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.13,0:15:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,為何\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,因為胡克永不滿足的求知慾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hooke's insatiable curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.40,0:15:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,覆蓋了所有的領域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}encompassed absolutely everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.57,0:15:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,胡克發現了一個小宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hooke discovered a little cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我們至今沿用他給它的命名  細胞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and we still call it by the name he gave it, the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}單詞原意：單人房
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.81,0:15:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,胡可通過觀察一片軟木片發現了細胞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hooke discovered the cell by looking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.61,0:15:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,正是用了他自己的一項發明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at a piece of cork with one of his own inventions,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.35,0:15:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,復合顯微鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the compound microscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.82,0:15:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他提出的觀點比達爾文的進化論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He anticipated aspects of Darwin's theory of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,早了幾乎200年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by almost 200 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.26,0:15:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,胡克又改良瞭望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hooke also improved the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.36,0:15:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,他根據觀察天體所做的素描\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The drawings he made of the astronomical bodies he observed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.00,0:15:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,見證了他異乎尋常的準確性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}attest to his uncanny precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.13,0:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,1666年的倫敦大火災摧毀了倫敦中部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After the Great Fire destroyed central London in 1666,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.64,0:15:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,胡克與建築師 克裏斯多佛·雷恩合作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hooke partnered with the architect Christopher Wren
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.44,0:15:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,重新設計 建設 倫敦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to redesign and rebuild the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.51,0:15:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,胡克是當時首屈一指的實驗主義者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hooke was the foremost experimentalist of his age.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.45,0:15:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,使用彈簧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Using coiled springs,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.82,0:15:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,他提出了 彈性定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he derived the "law of elasticity,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.55,0:15:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱之為  胡克定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}known today as Hooke's Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.05,0:15:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他改良了氣泵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He perfected the air pump,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.52,0:15:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,達到了當時的技術頂峰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the height of technology in its time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.89,0:16:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,並將之用於聲音和呼吸實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and used it to experiment on respiration and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.66,0:16:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他用大麻做實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he experimented with cannabis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.70,0:16:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他在一次皇家學會的會議上報告\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He reported to a meeting of the Royal Society
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.37,0:16:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,據他的一位船長朋友說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that a sea captain friend of his
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.04,0:16:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,「經常食用這個東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"had so often experimented with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不會令人產生恐懼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that there is no cause of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,只會帶來喜悅」\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}though possibly there may be of laughter."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.38,0:16:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,咖啡在17世紀的英格蘭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But coffee was the drug of choice for England
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.05,0:16:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,是最受歡迎的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the 17th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.55,0:16:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,咖啡館遍佈倫敦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Coffeehouses sprang up all over London.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,人們在那裏獲取新聞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is where people came to get news,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.44,0:16:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,發表新的觀點 討論時事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to launch new ventures, and to debate ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,咖啡館是這個注重階級的社會中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The coffeehouse was an oasis of equality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.58,0:16:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,平等的綠洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a class-obsessed society.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.25,0:16:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,在這裏  窮人不需要給富人讓座\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here, a poor man needn't give up his seat
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,也不用屈從他的觀點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a rich man, nor submit to his opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是民主制度的實驗室\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a kind of laboratory of democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.55,0:17:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在這種高度興奮刺激的氣氛中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In this highly caffeinated atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.22,0:17:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷和胡克 與克裏斯多佛·雷恩討論著一個謎團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley and Hooke met Christopher Wren to discuss a deep mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.96,0:17:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,為何行星如此運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why do the planets move as they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.40,0:17:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,天文學家約翰內斯·開普勒在此前的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The astronomer Johannes Kepler had demonstrated,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.93,0:17:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,80多年 就證明了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some 80 years before,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.43,0:17:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,行星繞太陽公轉的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the orbits of the planets around the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.04,0:17:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,並不是正圓  而是橢圓形\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were not perfect circles, but actually ellipses,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,行星越靠近太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and that the closer a planet was to the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,運動的越快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the faster it moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.71,0:17:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,會是太陽發出某些看不見的力量 導致這種變化嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Could some invisible force from the Sun be responsible for this change in motion?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是  又是如何導致的呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If so, how did it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.92,0:17:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,可以用一個簡單的數學定律描述嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Could there be a simple mathematical law to describe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,就像胡克的彈性定律那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe something like Hooke's Law of Elasticity?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.47,0:17:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,但是 嘗試之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But try as he might,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.10,0:17:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,克裏斯多佛·雷恩沒有答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Christopher Wren couldn't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.24,0:17:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,總好過沒有嘗試過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Damned if I haven't tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.77,0:17:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我的能力有限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's beyond me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.28,0:17:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我押上這本價值40先令的書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'll wager a book worth 40 shillings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:17:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,誰能解決 誰就拿去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the man who can solve it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.81,0:18:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我拿定了  雷恩先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That book is mine, Mr. Wren.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.95,0:18:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我已經完成了計算\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've already done the calculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.32,0:18:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷非常開心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley was delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,快讓我們見識見識  胡克先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Show us, Mr. Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.49,0:18:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,但幾個月過去  胡克也沒能做到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But months passed, and Hooke failed to deliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.09,0:18:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他算不過來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He couldn't do the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.76,0:18:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人能夠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}None of them could.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.59,0:18:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,最後 哈雷厭煩了胡克的借口\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Finally, Halley had enough of Hooke's excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.93,0:18:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷知道 肯定在某個地方 有某個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley knew there must be someone, somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.00,0:18:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,可以做到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}up to the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.31,0:18:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,劍橋大學的數學家怎麼樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What about that mathematician at Cambridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,聰明的傢伙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Clever fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.14,0:18:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他多年前就解決了光線本質的核心問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had solved central questions about the nature of light
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.51,0:18:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他當時只有22歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}years before, when he was still only 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他發明了反射望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he invented the reflecting telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,怪人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Odd bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.02,0:18:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,銷聲匿跡過一段時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Dropped out of sight a while back;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.19,0:18:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,對胡克本人和他的光學理論有些不同看法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some squabble over Hooke and his discovery about light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.33,0:18:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,走了極端  無法自拔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Went completely to pieces over it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.89,0:18:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,從此在劍橋大學隱居\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and has been hiding out in Cambridge ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.46,0:18:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷很期待 這個怪人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley wondered if this strange, and by all accounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,據說 很難相處的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}exceedingly difficult man, might succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:18:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,是否能成功\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where Hooke and others had failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.74,0:19:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他當時並不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What he couldn't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.31,0:19:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有任何人會想到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what no one could possibly imagine at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,整個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were the countless ways
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.84,0:19:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,就在1684年8月的某一天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the world would be forever changed by this meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.15,0:19:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,各個方面都因為這次見面 從此改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on an August day in 1684.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.02,0:19:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,艾薩克·牛頓出生於英格蘭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton was born in England
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.65,0:19:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,1642年的聖誕節\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on Christmas Day in 1642.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.86,0:19:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,父親在他出生前就過世了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before he even opened his eyes, his father was already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.83,0:19:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,3歲時 母親也拋棄了他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His mother left him when he was only three
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,直到11歲才再次見面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and did not return until he was 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.87,0:19:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,她已經有了新的家庭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When she did, it was with a new family and husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.67,0:19:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓鄙視他的繼父\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a stepfather who Isaac Newton despised.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,悲慘家庭環境中的唯一避風港\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton's refuge from his miserable family life
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.72,0:19:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,就是牛頓對於科學研究的熱情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was his passion to understand how things worked,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.56,0:19:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,特別是自然科學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}especially nature itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.76,0:20:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,1661年  天資聰穎的艾薩克進了劍橋大學三一學院\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1661, the talented young Isaac entered Trinity College at Cambridge University
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,他在學校很不合群\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where he was a consistently lousy student,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.17,0:20:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有家人和朋友\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one without friends or a loving family
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.00,0:20:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,給他絲毫的溫暖和鼓勵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to provide any warmth or encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.57,0:20:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓不與人交流  把自己關在房間裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton mostly kept to himself, sequestered in his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.24,0:20:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,學習古希臘的哲學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}studying ancient Greek philosophers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.75,0:20:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,幾何和語言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}geometry and languages,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.05,0:20:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,琢磨著更深層次的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and pondering deep questions
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.82,0:20:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,關於自然  空間  時間  運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the nature of matter, space, time, and motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.82,0:20:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,這位才華初露的科學家也是一名狂熱的神秘主義者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This budding scientist was also a passionate mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.53,0:20:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓相信這種只為小部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton believed that a secret knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.23,0:20:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,古代哲學家所知的煉金術\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}called alchemy, known only to a small group of ancient philosophers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.56,0:20:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,正等著他去重新發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was waiting to be rediscovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.60,0:20:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他希望可以學會把普通金屬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He hoped to learn how to change ordinary metals
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.27,0:20:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,變成金銀的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into silver and gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.91,0:20:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,或許可以做出生命合劑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and maybe even cook up the elixir of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.78,0:20:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,以此長生不老\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the key to to immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.91,0:20:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他一心想從聖經的字裏行間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was also obsessed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:20:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,找到隱藏的信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with finding hidden messages in the words of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.09,0:21:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他梳理了不用語言的譯本\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He combed through translations in several different languages,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.42,0:21:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,試圖破譯加密了的上帝的指示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hoping to decipher coded instructions from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.90,0:21:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他做了詳盡的計算\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He made elaborate calculations in an effort
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.13,0:21:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,只為發現基督再次降臨的日期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to discover the date of the Second Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.54,0:21:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,窮其一生研究煉金術\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His lifelong research in alchemy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.44,0:21:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,研究聖經  可惜沒有任何突破\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and biblical chronology never led anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.25,0:21:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,當哈雷找到牛頓的那天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Halley found Newton that fateful day,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.12,0:21:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓一直過著隱居的生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he was living as a virtual recluse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.06,0:21:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓自從羅伯特·胡克公開指責他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton had gone into hiding 13 years earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.00,0:21:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,剽竊胡克關於光學和顏色的突破性成果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}after Robert Hooke had publicly accused Newton of stealing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.67,0:21:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,已經隱居了13年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}his groundbreaking work on light and color.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.90,0:21:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 牛頓才是那個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, it was Isaac Newton
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.94,0:21:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,解開光譜謎團的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who solved the mystery of the spectrum of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.81,0:21:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,並不是羅伯特·胡克\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not Robert Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.61,0:21:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,這對他的打擊很大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This wound was painful and deep,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.78,0:22:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓下定決心從此再不讓自己陷入\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and Newton resolved to never expose himself to that kind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.58,0:22:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,那種被人羞辱的境地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of public humiliation ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.25,0:22:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,先生 你可能不記得了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sir, I don't suppose you recall
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.29,0:22:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我們幾年前見過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our meeting a few years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.32,0:22:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我記得 哈雷先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes, Mr. Halley.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉來打攪你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm sorry to bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.82,0:22:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,不用客套 有話直說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Never mind the formalities, get to your point.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.69,0:22:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直與我們的朋友  胡克和雷恩在討論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've been talking with our friends, Mr. Wren and Mr. Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.96,0:22:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,胡克那個人渣不是我的朋友\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That scoundrel Hooke's no friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.97,0:22:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我明白\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes, I understand, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.77,0:22:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,重點是 我們一直在討論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the thing is we've been debating
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.80,0:22:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,行星運動的難題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the puzzling question of planetary motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.71,0:22:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我們都認同 某種吸引的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We all agree that some force of attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.61,0:22:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,來自太陽  控制著行星的運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the Sun governs the motions of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.31,0:22:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我們感覺一定能有一條數學定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We suspect there must be a mathematical law
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.28,0:22:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,來形容這種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to describe how this force
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.95,0:22:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,根據距離而改變的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}changes with distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.45,0:22:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,以您的能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And knowing of your skill...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.79,0:22:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,沒錯 重力所產生的吸引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes, yes, the attraction of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.12,0:22:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,與距離的平方成反比\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}weakens with the square of the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.36,0:22:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是橢圓軌道的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why the planets move in ellipses.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.96,0:22:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,但您是怎麼知道的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But, sir, how can you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.56,0:22:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼了 我5年多前就算出來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why, I have calculated it some five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.50,0:22:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,求你了 讓我見識一下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I beg you, show it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.40,0:22:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,計算的結果在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The calculation is here...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.80,0:22:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,就在周圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,沒關係\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, no matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.04,0:23:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我重新做一份\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I shall redo it and be sure
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.51,0:23:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,然後寄給你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to send it on to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.58,0:23:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,太不可思議了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is stupendous!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.04,0:23:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,相見恨晚啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why have we not had word of it before?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.35,0:23:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓還記得上次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton remembered all too well
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.18,0:23:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他提出新的理論時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what Hooke had done to him
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.22,0:23:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,胡克的所作所為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the last time he put forth an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.89,0:23:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,就在哈雷開始懷疑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just when Halley may have begun to wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.99,0:23:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓是否也像胡克那樣吹牛時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if Newton was bluffing as Hooke had done earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,信使帶來牛頓的一封信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a messenger arrived with an envelope from Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.90,0:23:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,這是現代科學理論的開篇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here are the opening pages of modern science
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.70,0:23:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,包含了對於大自然的洞察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with its all-embracing vision of nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.01,0:23:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,運動定律  萬有引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}universal laws of motion, gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.78,0:23:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,不單適用於地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not just for the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.41,0:23:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,也適用於整個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but for the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.38,0:23:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷迫不及待地回到劍橋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley raced back to Cambridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.68,0:23:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓大人  我求你趕緊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mr. Newton, I beseech you to work all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.75,0:23:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,把這些都寫進你的書裏吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a book as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.36,0:23:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我向你保證 皇家學一定會出版你的書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can assure you the Royal Society will publish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.86,0:23:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,但還有一個小問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there was one little problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.73,0:23:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我們同意\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We are in agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.20,0:24:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓先生的成果是偉大的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that Mr. Newton has produced a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.37,0:24:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但是  皇家學會恐怕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}However, I'm afraid the Royal Society has...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.04,0:24:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,因為《魚類歷史》的慘淡銷售\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}well, regrettably sales for the History of Fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.98,0:24:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,造成我們的財政狀況並不樂觀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have not lived up to our financial expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.91,0:24:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一本很棒的書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's an impressive book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.75,0:24:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,包羅萬象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Extremely comprehensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.65,0:24:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,真的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.45,0:24:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,使用了大量的插圖來描述\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's filled with lavish illustrations of...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.99,0:24:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,魚類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}well, fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.46,0:24:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,銷量慘淡帶來更大的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The disappointing sales led to a bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.90,0:24:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,就是皇家學會在出版《魚類歷史》上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Royal Society pretty much blew
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.43,0:24:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎花了整年的預算\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its total annual budget on the History of Fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.43,0:24:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他們現金短缺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, they were so strapped for cash,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.17,0:24:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他們不得不用那賣不掉的書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they had to pay poor Halley's salary
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.61,0:24:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,來抵本應支付給哈雷的工資\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with copies of their worst-selling book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.31,0:24:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有錢來印刷牛頓的《原理》\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With no money to print Newton's Principia,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.51,0:24:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,科學革命 命懸一線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the scientific revolution hung in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.91,0:24:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,要不是哈雷的努力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Without Halley's heroic efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.89,0:24:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓的這部巨著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the reclusive Newton's masterwork
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.04,0:25:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,可能永無出頭之日\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}might never have seen the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.40,0:25:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷的堅持不懈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Halley was a man on a mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.60,0:25:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,將牛頓的天才展現給了全世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}absolutely determined to bring Newton's genius to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.21,0:25:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,那個科學革命以前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That pre-scientific world,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.78,0:25:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,靠恐懼來統治的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the world ruled by fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.25,0:25:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,已經被推向了革命的邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was poised at the edge of a revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.38,0:25:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,一切就看愛德蒙·哈雷能否\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everything depended on whether or not Edmond Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.75,0:25:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,將牛頓的新書推向世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could get Newton's book out to the wider world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.76,0:25:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷編輯並且出版了牛頓的書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley resolved not only to edit Newton's book,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.56,0:25:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,全都自掏腰包\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but to publish it at his own expense.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.56,0:25:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,在牛頓完成的頭兩卷裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton completed the first two volumes,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.46,0:25:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,用數學公式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}laying the mathematical framework
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.67,0:25:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,來描述物理運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the physics of motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.24,0:25:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,第三卷徹底決定了誰才是咖啡館的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The third volume would settle once and for all
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.27,0:25:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,賭局贏家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who won the coffeehouse wager.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓運用他的原理可以解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton applied his principles to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.41,0:25:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上所有的運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all the known motions of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.54,0:25:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,月亮和其他行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Moon and the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.91,0:25:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,不幸的是 還有一個問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unfortunately, there was this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.92,0:25:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷又變成了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now Halley also took on the role
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.75,0:25:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓的心理醫生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of Newton's psychotherapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.69,0:25:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,艾薩克  那個  胡克先生要求\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac, I'm afraid that Mr. Hooke requires
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.06,0:25:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在你的第三卷序言裏向他致謝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an acknowledgment in the preface of your third volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.39,0:26:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我已經做過了啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But I have done so.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.73,0:26:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,謝謝他 雷恩先生還有你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thanking him, Mr. Wren and yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.86,0:26:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,激勵我重新思考有關天文學的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for prodding me to think again on astronomical matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.97,0:26:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,胡克在倫敦到處說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mr. Hooke has been going about London saying
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.20,0:26:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你的萬有引力定律是借鑒了他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that you got the Law of Gravity from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.71,0:26:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我要告他這個小...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why, that litigious little...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.31,0:26:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,做夢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我寧可燒了我的第三卷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I would sooner burn the third volume
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.48,0:26:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,也不會讓這種謊言玷污它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than deface it with such a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.48,0:26:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,讓胡克去死吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To hell with Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.95,0:26:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他會被人們遺忘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He will be long forgotten
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.28,0:26:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,而你的理論會被人們永遠歌頌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when your ideas are still being celebrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.45,0:26:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,又是這些噁心的書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}More copies of that dreadful book?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.56,0:26:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,家裏都快放不下了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wherever shall we put them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.29,0:26:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我和你說過的 瑪麗 親愛的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We talked about this, Mary, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.83,0:26:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,這是科學院給我的薪水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is my salary from the Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.50,0:26:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他們也拿不出其他東西了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They have nothing else with which to pay me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.30,0:26:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,如果胡克和牛頓也能像你這樣就好了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If only Mr. Hooke and Mr. Newton were more like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.60,0:26:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷和雷恩決定和胡克對質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley and Wren decided to confront Hooke
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.61,0:26:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,關於他不實的言論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about his false claims.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.27,0:26:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我的定律 我告訴你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That law is mine, I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.91,0:26:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我先證明的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I proved it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.28,0:26:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,那就把你的證據拿出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then fetch your proof here at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.11,0:26:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們看看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let us see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.35,0:26:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,反正我們都等了這麼久了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Surely we have waited on it long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.95,0:27:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你只要相信我的話就可以了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You'll simply have to take my word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.09,0:27:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,空口無憑或許在其他地方行得通\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Empty claims may persuade elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.49,0:27:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,但這裏不行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.49,0:27:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}"勿輕信人言"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.69,0:27:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,拿不出來就閉嘴  胡克先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Put up or shut up, Mr. Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.20,0:27:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓這個混蛋  我要他付出代價\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Blasted Newton. I'll make him pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.50,0:27:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}"自然哲學的數學原理"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.35,0:27:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,如果沒有愛德蒙·哈雷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If it wasn't for Edmond Halley,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.82,0:27:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓絕沒有機會構思\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton's great book would've never been conceived,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.99,0:27:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,書寫 出版他的書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}nor written, nor printed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.52,0:27:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  那又怎樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay. So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.83,0:27:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,對我們來說有什麼不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What difference does that make to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.99,0:27:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,有什麼大不了的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.04,0:27:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,當牛頓在這棟房子裏誕生時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Isaac Newton was born in this house
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.21,0:27:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,1642年  那是的世界和現在完全不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in 1642, the world was very different.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.88,0:27:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,每個人看到天空中的眾多星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everyone looked at the perfection
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.11,0:27:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,像鐘錶一樣極有規律的準確運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the clockwork motions of the planets in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.78,0:28:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,只能想到的是出自\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and could only understand it as the work
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.72,0:28:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,一個偉大的「鐘錶匠」\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a master clock maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.38,0:28:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,還能怎麼解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How else to explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.49,0:28:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他們只能想出一種解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There was only one way such a thing could come about
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.86,0:28:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,以他們的想像力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in their imagination;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.32,0:28:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一種答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}only one answer for them--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.36,0:28:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.83,0:28:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,出於我們還不瞭解的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For reasons beyond our understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.13,0:28:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝就是這麼創造的太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}God just created the solar system that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.70,0:28:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,這個解釋卻是一個死結\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But this explanation is the closing of a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.67,0:28:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,並無法解釋其他的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It doesn't lead to other questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.35,0:28:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Along came Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.68,0:28:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝寵愛的人  大天才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a God-loving man who's also a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.82,0:28:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他能用完美的數學語句\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He could write the laws of nature
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.99,0:28:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,寫出大自然的定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in perfect mathematical sentences--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.42,0:28:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,對宇宙有效的方程式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}formulas that applied universally
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.89,0:28:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,對蘋果 月亮 行星都有效\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to apples, moons, planets
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.86,0:28:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,還有很多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and so much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.07,0:28:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然仍身處中世紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With one foot still in the Middle Ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.94,0:28:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓已經想像出了整個太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton imagined the whole solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.21,0:29:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓的萬有引力和運動定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton's laws of gravity and motion
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.58,0:29:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,揭示了太陽如何維繫這些遙遠的星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}revealed how the Sun held distant worlds captive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.45,0:29:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他的定律使人們不再需要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His laws swept away the need
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.61,0:29:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,用「鐘錶匠」來解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a master clock maker
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.25,0:29:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼太陽系能如此精準的運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to explain the precision and beauty of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.72,0:29:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,萬有引力就是鐘錶匠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gravity is the clock maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.96,0:29:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,事物遵循我們發現的戒律運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Matter obeyed commandments we could discover,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.36,0:29:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,遵循聖經沒有提到過的定律運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}laws the Bible hadn't mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.96,0:29:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓的理論解釋了為什麼太陽子會是這樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton's answer to why the solar system is the way it is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.97,0:29:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,也為其他無數的問題打開了大門\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}opened the way to an infinite number of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.54,0:29:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,《原理》的內容裏包括\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Principia also happened to include
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.57,0:29:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,微積分的發明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the invention of calculus,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.57,0:29:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,還有第一個堅實的理論基礎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the first sound theoretical basis
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.21,0:29:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,為我們打破了地球的枷鎖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for an end to our imprisonment on Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.71,0:29:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,太空旅行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}space travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.28,0:29:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓設想 發射出去的炮彈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton envisioned the firing of a cannonball...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.76,0:29:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,隨著爆炸推力的增加\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with increasingly greater explosive thrust.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.73,0:29:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,只要速度足夠快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He reasoned that with enough velocity,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.13,0:29:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,就可以突破引力的界限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the bounds of gravity could be broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.73,0:30:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,炮彈就可以離開地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the cannonball could escape
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.67,0:30:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,繞地球旋轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to orbit the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.00,0:30:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這 改變了 整個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This changed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.04,0:31:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓的數學原理 將我們徹底解放\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton's Principia Mathematica set us free in another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.64,0:31:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,通過找到控制彗星運行的自然定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By finding the natural laws governing the comings and goings of comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.34,0:31:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他使我們不再像祖先那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he decoupled the motions of the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.48,0:31:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,恐懼天體運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from their ancient connections to our fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.90,0:31:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,如果哈雷沒有竭盡全力的支持牛頓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If Halley hadn't been standing next to Newton for all those years,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.21,0:31:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,人們可能會記住他自己的發現和成就\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}perhaps the world would remember him for his own accomplishments and discoveries.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.25,0:31:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是 僅僅記住一個彗星的名字\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the only thing that comes to mind for most people
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.39,0:31:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,諷刺的是  發現彗星這件事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is the comet, the irony is that discovering a comet
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.87,0:31:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,其實哈雷從沒有做過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is actually one of the few things that Halley never did.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.03,0:31:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,有冰山\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mountain of ice to starboard
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.16,0:31:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,左滿舵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Come about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.66,0:32:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,報告哈雷隊長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Aye, aye, Captain Halley!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.43,0:32:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,《原理》出版後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After the publication of the Principia
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.08,0:32:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷奉命帶領3艘大船  出海科學考察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley was commanded by his king to lead three ocean voyages,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.97,0:32:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,為英國海軍解決導航的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}scientific expeditions to solve navigational problems for the British navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.54,0:32:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷利用這次機會  繪製了第一張地球磁場圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley used this opportunity to make the first map of the Earth's magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.93,0:32:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他同時也是個商人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he was also a businessman.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.90,0:32:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷改良了潛水鐘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley perfected the diving bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.24,0:32:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,並用他的發明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...and used his invention to start
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.37,0:32:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,開創了繁榮的商業打撈業務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a flourishing commercial salvage operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.72,0:32:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 哈雷博士這次是真的做到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mmm, ah, Dr. Halley's gone and done it this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.92,0:32:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我看他在下面最少3個小時了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I reckon he's been down there at least three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.15,0:32:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人拿其他人的生命冒險\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not one to risk the lives of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.89,0:32:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷親自測試他的發明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley personally tested his own invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.93,0:32:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,下來以後已經堅持了4個小時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I make it exactly four hours since our descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.47,0:33:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,對10英尋的深度來說不錯了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not at all bad for ten fathoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.47,0:33:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}10英尋等於約18米
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.91,0:33:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,他發明了氣象圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He invented the weather map.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.61,0:33:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他設計的標示盛行風的符號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the symbols he devised for indicating prevailing winds
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.18,0:33:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,一直沿用至今\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are still in use today.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.62,0:33:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}星期一天氣預測\n世界天氣
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.33,0:33:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷為人口統計學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley laid the groundwork
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.00,0:33:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,打下了堅實的基礎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the science of population statistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.10,0:33:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼做的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.43,0:33:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他對比倫敦和巴黎的出生 結婚 死亡人數\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He compared the birth, marriage, death,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.44,0:33:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,以及人口密度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and population densities of London and Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.34,0:33:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他真的用雙腳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He actually had to pace off
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.64,0:33:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,測量出巴黎的周長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the entire perimeter of Paris, on foot,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.81,0:33:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,只為計算正確的面積\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to learn its true dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.05,0:33:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他總結出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He came to the conclusion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.45,0:33:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,既然大約一半的成年人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that since roughly half of all adults fail
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.18,0:33:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,無法生孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to reproduce children,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.65,0:33:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,要延續他們繁衍的基因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who themselves survive to reproduce,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.65,0:33:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,每對夫妻必須要有4個孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every married couple must have four children
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.56,0:33:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,才能保持人口數量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in order to maintain the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.03,0:34:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,愛德蒙 哈雷告訴我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it was Edmond Halley who gave us
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.66,0:34:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽系的實際比例\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the actual scale of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.30,0:34:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他找到一個聰明的辦法算出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He figured out a clever way to find the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.87,0:34:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,地球到太陽的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from Earth to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.40,0:34:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,通過精確地測量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It involved precisely measuring the time it took
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.67,0:34:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,金星穿過日面所用的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the planet Venus to cross the Sun's disc.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.67,0:34:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即金星凌日
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.98,0:34:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷過世後的27年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}27 years after Halley's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.81,0:34:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,詹姆士庫克船長第一次到達塔希提島\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Captain James Cook made his first voyage to Tahiti
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.18,0:34:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,為了驗證哈雷的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the express purpose of testing Halley's method
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.75,0:34:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在觀察在金星凌日的過程中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}during a transit of Venus across the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.36,0:34:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他用一種特殊的濾鏡保護眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Using a special filter to protect his vision
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.76,0:34:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,防止直視太陽帶來的損傷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from being destroyed by looking directly at the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.93,0:34:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,庫克團隊的努力使我們知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cook and his men made it possible for us to know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.66,0:34:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}約為1.5億公里
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.66,0:34:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽距離地球9300萬英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the Sun is 93 million miles from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.00,0:34:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷也是第一個認識到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And Halley was the first to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.40,0:34:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,所謂的恆星 並非靜止不動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the so-called "fixed" stars were not fixed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.28,0:34:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他是怎麼知道的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How'd he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.08,0:34:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他將古希臘天文學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He pored over the observations made
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.68,0:34:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,對最明亮的星星的觀測結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the ancient Greek astronomers of the brightest stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.35,0:34:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,與他在1800年後觀測的同一顆星星的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he compared their observations with the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.08,0:35:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,觀測結果作比較\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he himself made of the same stars 1,800 years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.12,0:35:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼之前沒人注意到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why hadn't anyone noticed this before?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.39,0:35:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷意識到要想觀察出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley figured out that it would only become apparent
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.39,0:35:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,兩次的觀測時間要間隔很長才行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if you waited long enough between observations.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.53,0:35:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,要觀察到相距遙遠的物體間的移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's hard to perceive the motions of things
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.07,0:35:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,是很困難的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that are far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.40,0:35:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,而且恆星間的距離是如此的遙遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the stars are so very far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.10,0:35:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,要花幾百年的時間去觀察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that you would need to track them for many centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.44,0:35:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,才能察覺他們的移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before you could detect that they moved at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.71,0:35:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷發現了一個宏偉的現實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley discovered the first clue to a magnificent reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.38,0:35:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的恆星都在運動 相互趕超\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all the stars are in motion, streaming past each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.82,0:35:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,和旋轉木馬一樣上升和降落\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rising and falling like merry-go-round horses
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.49,0:35:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,在銀河系中此起彼伏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in their Newtonian dance around the center of our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.76,0:35:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,對了 還有彗星的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And, oh, yes, there was that thing about the comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.74,0:35:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,這些美麗的陌生天外訪客到底是誰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What were those strange and beautiful celestial visitors
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.24,0:35:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,時不時的突然造訪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that appeared without warning from time to time?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.84,0:35:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷用偵探常用的方法來解決這個謎團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley set out to solve this mystery as a detective would,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.95,0:36:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,搜集所有可靠目擊證人的證詞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by gathering all credible eyewitness testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.28,0:36:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷能找到的最早準確觀察到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The earliest precise observations of a comet
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.85,0:36:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星的證人是位於君士坦丁堡的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that Halley could find were made in Constantinople
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.75,0:36:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,尼斯波羅斯·貴格列 拜占庭帝國的天文學家兼僧人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by Nikephoros Gregoras, a Byzantine astronomer and monk
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.09,0:36:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,1337年6月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in June 1337.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.36,0:36:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷收集了1472-1698年間所有的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley hunted down every astronomical observation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.66,0:36:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,在歐洲的彗星觀測記錄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a comet recorded in Europe between 1472 and 1698.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.54,0:36:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,請記住 那時還沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And remember, there was no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.64,0:36:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,搜索引擎 或者電腦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a search engine or a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.47,0:36:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷只能依靠他的書和大腦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All Halley had were his books and his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.71,0:36:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,困難的地方到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now here comes the hard part,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.55,0:36:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷必須要按照每個彗星的觀察結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley had to take the observations made for each comet
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.55,0:36:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,在太空中的找出實際的運動軌跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and find the shape of its actual path through space.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.69,0:36:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,除了牛頓 沒人嘗試過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No one else but Newton had yet attempted
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.79,0:36:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,將他的定律應用於天文學的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to apply his new set of laws to an astronomical question.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.13,0:36:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一次艱巨的數學運算的壯舉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In an arduous tour de force of mathematical brilliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.46,0:36:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷發現彗星被太陽束縛在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley discovered that comets were bound to the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.83,0:36:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,長橢圓的軌道上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in long elliptical orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.87,0:37:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他是第一個知道1531年發現的那個彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he was the first to know that the comets seen in 1531,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.54,0:37:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,和1607年 還有1682年發現的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}1607, and 1682...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.42,0:37:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是同一顆彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were one and the same--
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.42,0:37:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,每隔76年回歸一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a single comet that returned every 76 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.66,0:37:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,這是識別規律的絕佳例子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In a stunning example of true pattern recognition,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.03,0:37:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他預測彗星還會回歸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he predicted it would be seen again
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.03,0:37:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在超過50年後的未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more than 50 years in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.90,0:37:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,上千年來 彗星都很神秘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For millennia, comets had been props for mystics,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.00,0:37:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,被巫師們視為人類事件的預兆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who considered them to be merely omens of human events.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.61,0:37:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷打破了他們的壟斷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley shattered their monopoly,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.41,0:37:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,以他們熟悉的領域裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}beating them at their own game,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.88,0:37:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,以前沒有科學家進入過的領域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a game that no scientist had ever played before...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.55,0:37:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,預言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.25,0:37:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他沒有閃爍其詞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he did not hedge his bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.59,0:37:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,就像貝比·魯斯預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like Babe Ruth predicting
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.19,0:37:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他的下一個全壘打會落在哪裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where his next home run would land in the stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.02,0:37:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷明確地指出這顆彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley stated flatly that the comet would return
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.96,0:37:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,會在1758年底 出現在天空中的一個特定位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the end of 1758, from a particular part of the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.56,0:37:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,遵循一條特定的軌跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}following a specific path.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.87,0:38:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎沒有一個由巫師提出的預言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There is hardly a prophecy attempted by the mystics
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.64,0:38:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,能和他的準確性相提並論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that ever even strives for comparable precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.13,0:38:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是 哈雷彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's Halley's Comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.20,0:38:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,漂浮在太陽系的邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Out here at the edge of the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.64,0:38:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去並不大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it doesn't look like much.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.04,0:38:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,只是太空中一塊冰石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just a big hunk of ice and rock in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.54,0:38:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,因為在海王星的軌道以外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's because beyond the orbit of Neptune,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.58,0:38:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,距離太陽大約50億公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}nearly five billion kilometers from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.08,0:38:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星過得非常寧靜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}comets lead very quiet lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.05,0:38:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,因為到達了軌道的遠端\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As it reaches the far end of its orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.36,0:38:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,它會慢下來 直到太陽將它拉回來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it'll slow down till the Sun allows it to go no farther.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.36,0:38:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,然後它向太陽系的核心墜落\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then it will begin its long fall back to the inner solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.06,0:38:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷彗星繞著太陽做自由落體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley's comet is in free fall around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.70,0:39:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽系中的一切  地球  月亮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everything in our solar system-- the Earth, the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.07,0:39:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,其他行星  彗星  小行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the other planets, comets, asteroids,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.17,0:39:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,都繞著太陽自由落體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all of them are falling around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.41,0:39:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,萬有引力將他們拉向太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gravity pulls the planets towards the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.45,0:39:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但因為他們的軌道動量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but because of their orbital momentum,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.38,0:39:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他們保持環繞太陽  而不衝向太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they keep moving around the Sun, never falling into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.39,0:39:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,羅伯特·胡克很多年前過世了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Robert Hooke had died years before,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.56,0:39:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,一些壞習慣傷害了他的健康\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}having ruined his health with some bad habits...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.36,0:39:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,天天服用苦艾 鴉片 水銀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}daily doses of wormwood, opium, mercury.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.40,0:39:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,幾個月後  牛頓取代了他的職位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A few months later, Newton was elected to replace him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.57,0:39:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,當選皇家學會的會長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as president of the Royal Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.80,0:39:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,據說胡克的肖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It is said that a portrait of Hooke
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.57,0:39:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經掛在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}once hung on these walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.38,0:39:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷達成了很多天文學的豐功偉績\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley lived on to accomplish many more astonishing feats.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.91,0:39:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他堅持工作到最後一刻 享年85歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He worked right up to his death at age 85.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.58,0:39:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,他做的最後一件事是叫了一杯葡萄酒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His final act was to call for a glass of wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.12,0:39:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,愉快的品下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He downed it with pleasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.49,0:39:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,呼出最後一口氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and breathed his last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.76,0:40:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,據信在這樣的一個夜裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some believe that it was on a night like this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.77,0:40:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,艾薩克牛頓終於實施了他對\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that Isaac Newton finally took his revenge
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.77,0:40:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,羅伯特胡克的報復\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}against Robert Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.15,0:40:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷的預言並未被人遺忘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Halley's prophecy was not forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.66,0:40:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,50年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}50 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.26,0:40:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,就在預言回歸的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the time of the predicted return approached,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.93,0:40:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,全世界的天文學家都希望\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the world's astronomers vied
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.70,0:40:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,第一個觀察到 哈雷的彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to be the first to catch sight of his comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.60,0:40:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他們沒有失望\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They weren't disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.20,0:40:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,從此以後 每隔76年都有一次觀測熱潮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's been welcomed back every 76 years since.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.47,0:40:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,當哈雷彗星回到我們的天空時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Halley's Comet returns to our skies,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.88,0:40:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,日光加熱它表面的冰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sunlight will warm up the ice on its surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.95,0:40:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,再一次釋放出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}once again setting loose
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.95,0:40:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,內部的灰塵和氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the dust and gases trapped within.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.82,0:41:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,哈雷彗星的最近一次回歸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Halley's Comet most recently visited our neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.32,0:41:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,是1986年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}back in 1986.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.19,0:41:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你在2061年看到這個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And if you're seeing this in 2061,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.29,0:41:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你就知道 它回來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then you'll know it's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.80,0:41:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,願你看到眼前的這些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}May you feel the wonder of all those
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.67,0:41:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,令人驚嘆的奇跡時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who came before you...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.07,0:41:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,不再害怕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and none of the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.07,0:41:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓定律使愛德蒙哈雷可以預見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton's laws made it possible for Edmond Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.71,0:41:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,50年後的未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to see some 50 years into the future
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.41,0:41:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,預測一顆彗星的運動軌跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and predict the behavior of a single comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.41,0:41:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,科學家們一直使用這些定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Scientists have been using these laws ever since,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.75,0:41:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,打開通往月球之路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}opening the way to the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.65,0:41:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,乃至整個太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and even beyond our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.69,0:41:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,搖籃中的嬰兒開始學習走路了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The baby in the basket is learning to walk...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.90,0:41:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,開始瞭解宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to know the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.31,0:41:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,還有最後一個預言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Which brings me to one last prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.68,0:41:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,僅僅依靠牛頓的萬有引力定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Using nothing more than Newton's laws of gravitation,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.85,0:42:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,天文學家可以很確定的預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we astronomers can confidently predict
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.55,0:42:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,幾十億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that several billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.85,0:42:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的星系  銀河系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our home galaxy, the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.59,0:42:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,會與我們的鄰居 僊女座 交匯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will merge with our neighboring galaxy Andromeda.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.46,0:42:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,因為恆星間的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because the distances between the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.70,0:42:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,相對他們的體積來說 是如此的遙遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are so great compared to their sizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.06,0:42:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,只會有很少數的星星發生碰撞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}few if any stars in either galaxy will actually collide.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.53,0:42:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,遙遠未來 依然存在的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Any life on the worlds of that far-off future
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.47,0:42:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,應該很安全  但是他們可以欣賞到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}should be safe, but they would be treated to an amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.44,0:42:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,持續幾十億年的星光秀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}billion-year-long light show...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.45,0:42:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千億顆星星的群舞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a dance of a half a trillion stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.12,0:42:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一位偉人與他的摯友共同譜寫的精彩樂章\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to music first heard on one little world by a man who had but one true friend.
